#AzaCoverStory: Presenting @chitrangda — a striking blend of unconventional beauty and unshakable talent, redefining what it means to be a leading woman in Indian cinema.

“I love travelling and trying my hand at outdoor activities from scuba diving to golf and horse-riding.” There’s also a quiet, artistic side to her who sketches in charcoal and finds joy in the meditative patience of fishing, a hobby she explored during the lockdown. “It’s so relaxing,” she says. “Just you and the rhythm of the water.”

In this Aza exclusive, we celebrate a woman who’s never followed the crowd, but always stayed true to herself. Chitrangda isn’t here for the noise, she’s here for the nuance. And she’s doing it all, unapologetically, on her own terms. Link in bio.

latestPosts.caption:
#AzaCoverStory: Presenting @chitrangda . When Chitrangda Singh first stepped into the limelight, she quietly rewrote the rules of conventional beauty in Indian cinema. Her distinct features, often labeled “exotic,” weren’t just accepted, they were celebrated.

2011 marked a defining moment for the cover star: her breakout into mainstream cinema with Desi Boyz opposite Akshay Kumar. Over the years, she’s carved a path uniquely her own, choosing roles that defy stereotypes and narratives that speak louder than just box office numbers. From Sudhir Mishra’s Inkaar, a gripping romantic thriller, to the slick financial drama Baazaar with #Saifalikhan, and more recently, the compelling OTT series Khakee: The Bengal Chapter- her choices reflect not only range, but intent.

In this Aza exclusive, we celebrate a woman who’s never followed the crowd, but always stayed true to herself. Chitrangda isn’t here for the noise, she’s here for the nuance. And she’s doing it all, unapologetically, on her own terms. Link in bio.
